cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DS

This paper is about the Second International Competition on Computational Models of Argumentation, which is a major topic in the study of Artificial Intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The competition involves solving (abstract) argumentation frameworks, which involves reasoning and decision making, making cs.LG and cs.CL also likely sub-categories. The competition also involves assessing advancements in problem solving technologies, which could fall under cs.CR. Finally, the competition involves organizing tasks and tracks, which could involve data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS a possible sub-category as well.
